    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - TESTING
        INTERVISION CIRCUITS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING INTERVISION CIRCUITS</title>
        <table id="t0821218" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing InterVision Circuits</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.97in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.33in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Does the InterVision module have a visible display?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to Step 6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect the InterVision display connector (1156). Turn ignition on, and measure
                                voltage from circuit 13M to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13M to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 13M, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure voltage from circuit 13M to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13M to 11-GK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 11-GK, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Measure voltage from circuit 14B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>14B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 14B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With headlights on and panel lights all the way up, measure voltage from circuit 62W
                                to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>62W to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Power circuits check good. Replace InterVision module.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 62W, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Does the InterVision display show a problem receiving data from the data link?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Display shows problem with data link.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>If InterVision is not working correctly, replace the module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect data link pos. connector (514) and data link neg. connector (515). At
                                (1156), measure resistance from circuit 98H(-) and 98G (+) to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1156), 98H(-) and 98G (+) to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Open circuit.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 98H(-) or 98G (+), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Connect a jumper between data link pos. connector (514), cavity F and data link neg.
                                connector (515), cavity F. At (1156), measure resistance between circuit 98H(-) and 98G
                                (+).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1156), 98H(-) and 98G (+).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Data link circuits check good. Go to next step to check RS- 232 circuits.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 98H(-) or 98G (+), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At (1156), measure resistance from circuits 91A and 91 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1156), 91A, 91 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Open circuit.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuits 91A and 91, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Connect a jumper between RS-232 connector (1170), circuit 91A and circuit 91. At
                                (1156), measure resistance between circuit 91A and 91.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1156), 91A and 91.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 91A or 91, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Connect a jumper between RS-232 connector (1170), circuit 91A and circuit 91-G. At
                                (1156), measure resistance between circuit 91A and 91-G.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(1156), 91A and 91-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>All Inter- Vision circuits check good. Replace Inter- Vision module.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 91A or 91-G, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
